{"id":23665,"date":"2022-02-10T14:58:58","date_gmt":"2022-02-10T13:58:58","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.mannheimerswartling.se\/?page_id=23665"},"modified":"2025-01-15T13:26:38","modified_gmt":"2025-01-15T12:26:38","slug":"law-scholarship","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/www.mannheimerswartling.se\/en\/career\/student-opportunities\/law-scholarship\/","title":{"rendered":"Law Scholarship"},"content":{"rendered":"<p class=\"preamble\">The foundation, Avstamp f\u00f6r Juridiska Studier, awards scholarships of SEK 10,000 each year to at least one student who has commenced their Law studies at a Swedish university and who comes from a non-academic family background.<\/p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-23035 alignnone\" src=\"https:\/\/www.mannheimerswartling.se\/app\/uploads\/2022\/12\/03-0136-1200x800.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.mannheimerswartling.se\/app\/uploads\/2022\/12\/03-0136-1200x800.jpg 1200w, https:\/\/www.mannheimerswartling.se\/app\/uploads\/2022\/12\/03-0136-2000x1333.jpg 2000w, https:\/\/www.mannheimerswartling.se\/app\/uploads\/2022\/12\/03-0136-800x533.jpg 800w, https:\/\/www.mannheimerswartling.se\/app\/uploads\/2022\/12\/03-0136-768x512.jpg 768w, https:\/\/www.mannheimerswartling.se\/app\/uploads\/2022\/12\/03-0136-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https:\/\/www.mannheimerswartling.se\/app\/uploads\/2022\/12\/03-0136-2048x1365.jpg 2048w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" \/><\/p>\n<p>To be eligible to apply, you must have been accepted to a Law program at one of the universities in Sweden and be studying in your first, second or third semester. The scholarship is aimed at those who come from non-academic families which, in this context, means that neither parent has a Swedish university education.<\/p>\n<h4>The application<\/h4>\n<p>Your application should consist of a personal cover letter, accompanied by an acceptance letter or other certificate showing that you have been admitted to and are studying Law at a university in Sweden. Applications should be sent by email to Fredrik Svensson, founder of the scholarship and a partner at Mannheimer Swartling, via <a href=\"mailto:avstamp@msa.se\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">avstamp@msa.se<\/a>.<\/p>\n<h4>Application period for the 2025 scholarship<\/h4>\n<p>1 January \u2013 31 October 2025.<\/p>\n<p>More details about the scholarship can be found <a href=\"https:\/\/www.mannheimerswartling.se\/app\/uploads\/2025\/01\/Stipendiestiftelsen-Avstamp-2025.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">here<\/a>.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>The foundation, Avstamp f\u00f6r Juridiska Studier, awards scholarships of SEK 10,000 each year to at least one student who has commenced their Law studies at\u2026<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":10,"featured_media":0,"parent":13552,"menu_order":6,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","template":"","meta":{"_acf_changed":false,"footnotes":""},"class_list":["post-23665","page","type-page","status-publish","hentry"],"acf":[],"lang":"en","translations":{"en":23665,"sv":20919},"pll_sync_post":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.mannheimerswartling.se\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/23665"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.mannheimerswartling.se\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.mannheimerswartling.se\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/page"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.mannheimerswartling.se\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/10"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.mannheimerswartling.se\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=23665"}],"version-history":[{"count":6,"href":"https:\/\/www.mannheimerswartling.se\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/23665\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":29459,"href":"https:\/\/www.mannheimerswartling.se\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/23665\/revisions\/29459"}],"up":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.mannheimerswartling.se\/